    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                <head>No. 241.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CEDL1" type="to">De
                                Long</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 29, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 133.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr. Shephard’s dispatch of July 20, 1872,
                        relating to his refusal to render assistance or protection to the Peruvian
                        bark Maria Luz, was duly received. As that vessel was engaged in the coolie
                        trade the proceedings of Mr. Shephard, as reported in that dispatch, are
                        approved.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HF1">Hamilton Fish</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
